pageContext.claim: “As you know, it's about 600 cases, it's about 26 deaths, within our country. And had we not acted quickly, that number would have been substantially more.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump started moving the goalposts here in terms of assessing his track record on the coronavirus, after weeks of touting just 15 cases. The administration had failed to act quickly to ramp up testing of potential patients, missing a chance to stem the spread of the infection.
